best authentic belgian waffle recipe i went to belgium and they had awesome waffles i want a recipe so i can make them here in the states they looked like these http en wikipedia org wiki image gaufre liege jpg my personal favourite classic belgian waffles cups cake flour teaspoons baking powder teaspoon salt large eggs separated tablespoons sugar teaspoon vanilla extract tablespoons unsalted butter melted cups milk non stick cooking spray preheat the waffle iron according to the manufacturer's instructions in medium bowl sift together flour baking powder and salt set aside in a second bowl use the wooden spoon to beat together the egg yolks and sugar until sugar is completely dissolved and eggs have turned a pale yellow add the vanilla extract melted butter and milk to the eggs and whisk to combine combine the egg milk mixture with the flour mixture and whisk just until blended do not over mix in third bowl beat the egg whites with an electric mixer until soft peaks form about minute using the rubber spatula gently fold the egg whites into the waffle batter do not overmix coat the waffle iron with non stick cooking spray and pour enough batter in iron to just cover waffle grid close and cook as per manufacturer's instructions until golden brown about to minutes serve immediately this is how my mom likes it belgian waffles c heavy cream tbsp superfine sugar teaspoon vanilla extract waffle batter c sifted cake flour tsp baking powder c sugar pinch of salt egg yolks c milk tsp vanilla extract c melted butter egg whites preheat a waffle iron whip the first three ingredients and place in refrigerator to chill sift together the flour baking powder c sugar and salt onto a piece of waxed paper beat the egg yolks lightly and add the milk vanilla and melted butter drop in the dry ingredients and stir just enough to combine in a separate clean bowl beat the egg whites until they are stiff but not dry and fold them into the batter gently bake in a seasoned waffle iron at medium heat until the steam stops escaping dust the baked waffles with confectioner's sugar and top with whipped cream sliced strawberries or peaches may be served on top Dairy Idli Cuisine of Denmark Recipe Chili con carne Breakfast Waffle Puff pastry Cold Stone Creamery German cuisine Rice pudding Bacon Cuisine of the Southern United States Baked Alaska Casting Cuisine of the Philippines Custard Vanilla Soup Scrambled eggs Milk Dosa French toast Cantonese cuisine Kit Kat Cuisine of Brazil Soy protein Souffl__ Ramen Dim sum Sugar Cuisine of Malaysia French fries Butter Mooncake Haggis Plastic Cajun cuisine Cheesecake Baking powder Potato pancakes Vinegar Sushi Pottery Bagel Fire extinguisher Chocolate Salty Balls Curry Soul food Sandwich Cuisine of Singapore Turkish Delight In-N-Out Burger B__chamel sauce Korean cuisine Cocoa Dumpling Cha chaan teng Japanese tea ceremony Cheese Turkish coffee Egg (food) Baking Peruvian cuisine Maple syrup Thermal power station Gumbo Potato Internal ballistics Soap Risotto Confectionery Wine making Horehound Magnesium French cuisine 